"""
RadioML Modulation Classifier — v7
====================================
"SNR-Adaptive Cross-Attention Fusion of Complex IQ and
 Amplitude-Phase Streams with Higher-Order Cumulants
 for Automatic Modulation Classification"

NOVEL CONTRIBUTIONS
───────────────────
CONTRIBUTION 1 — Cross-stream attention at every scale
  Every published dual-stream AMC paper concatenates streams at the end.
  v7 inserts bidirectional cross-attention after each ResNet stage:
    IQ_out = IQ + CrossAttn(query=IQ, key/value=AP)
    AP_out = AP + CrossAttn(query=AP, key/value=IQ)
  Physical motivation: symbol transitions in IQ phase have a corresponding
  amplitude signature in AP that depends on modulation order. Cross-attention
  at each scale lets the model learn this hierarchically.

CONTRIBUTION 2 — SNR-adaptive fusion gate
  AP and IQ are not equally informative at all SNRs. A lightweight SNR
  estimator trained jointly outputs α ∈ [0,1] controlling:
    fused = (1-α)·IQ + α·AP
  At low SNR, amplitude is noise-dominated → model learns α→0.
  At high SNR, amplitude encodes constellation density → model learns α→1.
  Publishing α vs SNR curves per class is a novel interpretable result.

CONTRIBUTION 3 — Higher-Order Cumulants (HOC) branch
  HOCs are analytically computed statistical features that directly encode
  constellation geometry — they are provably discriminative for QAM16/64
  in ways that 128 IQ samples cannot reliably recover.

  Features computed per frame:
    C20 = E[z²]                   — 2nd order moment
    C21 = E[|z|²]                 — power
    C40 = E[z⁴] - 3·E[z²]²       — 4th order cumulant
    C41 = E[|z|²·z²] - 3·E[z²]·E[|z|²]
    C42 = E[|z|⁴] - |E[z²]|² - 2·E[|z|²]²
    C60, C61, C62, C63            — 6th order cumulants

  These 10 features (real-valued) are fed through a small MLP and fused
  with the BiLSTM output BEFORE the classifier head. This is the single
  highest-impact accuracy improvement available on RML2016.10a — papers
  adding HOC branches consistently show +2–4% on average accuracy.

ARCHITECTURE
────────────
  IQ Input ──[CV-Stem]──[CV-ResBlock]──[CrossAttn]──[CV-ResBlock]──[CrossAttn]──[CV-ResBlock]──[CrossAttn]──┐
  AP Input ──[Re-Stem]──[Re-ResBlock]──[CrossAttn]──[Re-ResBlock]──[CrossAttn]──[Re-ResBlock]──[CrossAttn]──┤
  IQ Input ──[SNR Estimator] ─────────────────────────────────────── α ─────────────────────────────────────┤
                                                                   SNR-Adaptive Gate (α·AP + (1-α)·IQ) ──────┤
                                                                   BiLSTM(128) ──────────────────────────────┤
                                                                   ChannelAttention ──────────────────────────┤
                                                                   GAP → (B, 256) ────────────────────────────┤
                                                                                                              │
  IQ Input ──[HOC Compute] → 10 features → MLP → (B, 64) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
                                                                                                              │
                                                             Concat[(B,256), (B,64)] → Dense → softmax ───────┘

  Auxiliary losses:
    total = focal(cls) + 0.1·mse(snr) 
"""

